<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="/images/favicon.png">
    <meta name="description"
        content="Build your own DIY entryway bench with storage. Our step-by-step guide walks you through the process of creating a functional and stylish bench for your home's foyer.">
    <title>DIY Entryway Bench with Storage - Home Hub</title>
    <script src="https://cdn.tailwindcss.com/3.4.16"></script>
    <script>
        tailwind.config = {
            theme: {
                extend: {
                    colors: {
                        primary: "#14B8A6",
                        secondary: "#0F766E",
                    },
                    borderRadius: {
                        none: "0px",
                        sm: "4px",
                        DEFAULT: "8px",
                        md: "12px",
                        lg: "16px",
                        xl: "20px",
                        "2xl": "24px",
                        "3xl": "32px",
                        full: "9999px",
                        button: "8px",
                    },
                },
            },
        };
    </script>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Pacifico&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/remixicon/4.6.0/remixicon.min.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/responsive.css">
</head>

<body class="bg-white">
    <%- include("../partials/header") %>

        <main class="py-8 bg-white">
            <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
                    <article class="lg:col-span-2">
                        <div class="bg-white">
                            <nav class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">
                                <a href="/" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">Home</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <a href="/diy-projects" class="hover:text-primary transition-colors">DIY Projects</a>
                                <span class="mx-2">></span>
                                <span class="text-gray-800">DIY Entryway Bench</span>
                            </nav>

                            <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">
                                How to Build a DIY Entryway Bench with Storage
                            </h1>

                            <div class="mb-8">
                                <img src="/images/diy-entryway-bench.webp"
                                    alt="Finished DIY entryway bench with storage baskets"
                                    class="w-full h-80 object-cover rounded-lg shadow-lg" fetchpriority="high">
                            </div>

                            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Introduction</h2>
                                <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
                                    A bench in the entryway is a game-changer. It provides a spot to sit while putting
                                    on shoes and offers much-needed storage for everyday items. Building one yourself
                                    allows you to customize the size and finish to perfectly match your home.
                                </p>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Tools and Materials Needed</h2>
                                <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Lumber:</strong> 2x4s for the frame and 1x12s for the bench top and
                                        cubbies.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Tools:</strong> Circular saw, drill, Kreg jig (for pocket holes), and
                                        sander.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Hardware:</strong> Wood screws, wood glue, and your choice of paint or
                                        stain.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">The Building Process</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">Follow these general steps to create your custom entryway
                                    bench.</p>
                                <ul class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700 space-y-2 mb-6">
                                    <li><strong>Cut the Wood:</strong> Cut all your pieces according to your desired
                                        dimensions.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Assemble the Frame:</strong> Use pocket hole screws and glue for a
                                        sturdy base.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Add the Cubbies:</strong> Space them according to the baskets you plan
                                        to use.</li>
                                    <li><strong>Attach the Top:</strong> Secure the bench seat to the top of the frame.
                                    </li>
                                    <li><strong>Sand and Finish:</strong> Sand all surfaces smooth and apply your finish
                                        of choice.</li>
                                </ul>

                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-8 mb-4">Conclusion</h2>
                                <p class="text-gray-700">
                                    This project is a great way for beginners to practice basic woodworking skills while
                                    creating a piece of furniture that is both beautiful and functional.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </article>

                    <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
                        <div class="sticky top-8 space-y-6">
                            <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
                                <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Pro Woodworking Tip</h3>
                                <p class="text-gray-600">Always pre-drill your holes to prevent the wood from splitting,
                                    especially when working with soft woods like pine.</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </aside>
                </div>
            </div>
        </main>

        <%- include("../partials/footer") %>
            <script src="/js/script.js"></script>
</body>

</html>